This paper discusses the use of machine learning for malware detection and analysis in cloud computing environments, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically mentions recent advances in machine learning on graphs and natural language, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of federated learning for privacy-preserving inference and training, which suggests that it may fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses open problems related to designing robust ecosystems and developing machine learning models, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
